<dl id="n43097a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n43" href="#n43097a">N43 (VI.B.35)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n43all.htm#n43097a"> 97(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> aloefibre cloth</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Some of the more remarkable hieroglyphic-bearing monuments of the Mayas have been found in the palace of Palenque, the Spanish name of the old Yucatan capital. (&hellip;) Time and fanaticism have made sad havoc with the <font color="green">[Mayan]</font> manuscripts, and no satisfactory key to their decipherment has been found, only a few words here and there being interpreted. They were executed in bright and varied colours, with a feather pencil, on prepared skins, paper, or rolls of cotton or aloe-fibre cloth (&hellip;) <small> Edward Clodd, <a name="ECSA2" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ECSA2"><cite title="source">The Story of the Alphabet</cite></a>, rev. ed. (1913) 76 [Memory-aids and Picture-writing]</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
